* Miscellaneous small components

The total cost should be approximately $600–$700.

Once we have a collection of repeatable data, I think it may also be worth publishing the results internally through a small static site, possibly something like headsets.connect.com, similar to LandingPages. That would likely be cleaner than maintaining headset data across Smartsheet, Confluence, and Excel workbooks.

The site could become the source of truth for approved models, conditionally approved models, rejected models, test notes, headset-specific audio samples, transcription WER, known issues, FAQs, recommended softphone/WebRTC settings, and support guidance.

As a possible phase2, once we have enough test data and a narrowed-down device list, I’d also like to look at on-prem centralized headset firmware management. Almost all big name brands like Jabra, Epos, Poly/HP etc have solutions that can report firmware versions and push updates remotely and silently. It would be useful operationally because many headset-related issues come down to firmware mismatches between the headset, dongle, and softphone/WebRTC stack.

I would treat that as a separate follow-up effort since it would need POCs, planning, and InfoSec review and probably some endpoint/client management discussion. I just think it is worth mentioning now because the certification work and firmware lifecycle management are closely related.

If you’re okay with the approach, I can send over the parts list/BOM for review and we can decide the best path for purchasing or reimbursement.
